I created and updated my profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn and researchGate. These platforms are important for building a professional digital presence as a student.

GitHub is mainly used for storing, managing, and sharing coding projects. It helps students showcase their work and collaborate with others. 
I created my GitHub profile and added a README with my basic details and learning goals.

 LinkedIn is a professional networking platform where students can connect with peers, professors, and recruiters. 

ResearchGate is a social networking platform for scientists and researchers to share research, collaborate, and connect 

These platforms amplify your visibility and opportunities. GitHub showcases coding skills to potential employers. 
LinkedIn connects you with industry pros and job openings. ResearchGate builds your research network and citation impact. 
They collectively enhance your profile, foster collaborations, and open doors to internships, jobs, and research opportunities, setting you up for success
